# Pac-Man for LandTiger LPC1768

This project is an implementation of the classic **Pac-Man** video game for the **LandTiger LPC1768** development board, based on the **ARM Cortex-M3** architecture. It was developed as part of the **Computer Architectures** course for the MSc in Computer Engineering at **Politecnico di Torino**. The project utilizes several peripherals of the LandTiger board, including the **LCD display**, **buttons**, **joystick**, as well as timers such as the **Repetitive Interrupt Timer (RIT)** and the **general-purpose Timer**.

### Additional Project Requirements

For detailed project specifications and additional requirements, refer to the [requirements](extrapoint_1.pdf) document.